summary: This is an email chain from October 9, 2020, regarding the logistics of transferring a CD containing evidence for the Ghislaine Maxwell case. An agent plans to drop off the CD, and the recipient, working remotely, offers to connect the sender with another paralegal if the matter is time-sensitive.

events.title: CD Drop-off for Maxwell Case
events.description: An agent plans to drop off a CD containing files for the Ghislaine Maxwell case, with a request for it to be taken to IT to attempt to open the files.

keyFacts: A CD containing evidence for the Ghislaine Maxwell case was being transferred on October 9, 2020.
The email indicates operational logistics and chain of custody concerns for digital evidence in the Maxwell case.
The correspondence shows personnel were working remotely, possibly due to the COVID-19 pandemic or long weekend.
